import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Assuming you have a DataFrame df with columns "Airline name" and "Rating"

# Count the occurrences of each unique Airline name
airline_counts = df["Title"].value_counts()

# Get the unique Airline names
airline_names = airline_counts.index

# Create a bar plot
plt.figure(figsize=(16, 6))  # Adjust the figure size as needed
plt.bar(airline_names, airline_counts)
plt.xlabel("Airline Name")
plt.ylabel("Frequency")
plt.title("Distribution of Airline Names vs. Rating")
plt.xticks(rotation=45, fontsize=10)  # Rotate x-axis labels for readability

# Show the plot
plt.tight_layout()  # Ensure the labels fit within the figure
plt.show()

from nltk.sentiment.vader import SentimentIntensityAnalyzer

# Initialize the sentiment analyzer
analyzer = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()

# Calculate sentiment scores for each title
df["Sentiment"] = df["Title"].apply(lambda x: analyzer.polarity_scores(x))
